SciPy / Cephes derived special functions
----------------------------------------
Numeric code in `src/scipy/special.ml` derives from third-party sources that
JAX itself segregates and attributes. The attribution is retained here (the
no-comments rule of this project keeps it out of the sources).

  betaln, algdiv
    Ported from `jax._src.third_party.scipy.betaln`, which is derived from
    SciPy's cdflib routines `algdiv.f` and `betaln.f` (BSD-3-Clause):
    https://github.com/scipy/scipy/blob/c89dfc2b90d993f2a8174e57e0cbc8fbe6f3ee19/scipy/special/cdflib/algdiv.f
    https://github.com/scipy/scipy/blob/ef2dee592ba8fb900ff2308b9d1c79e4d6a0ad8b/scipy/special/cdflib/betaln.f

  ndtr, ndtri, log_ndtr
    Rational-approximation coefficients are from the Cephes Mathematical
    Library by Stephen Moshier. JAX redistributes the Cephes code under the
    Apache License 2.0 with the author's documented written consent
    ("Yes, Google may distribute Cephes files under the Apache 2 license.",
    Stephen Moshier). Reference:
    https://root.cern.ch/doc/v608/SpecFuncCephesInv_8cxx_source.html
    https://netlib.org/cephes/misc.tgz

  dawsn
    Rational approximations from Cody, Paciorek, Thacher (1970),
    "Chebyshev Approximations for Dawson's Integral", Math. Comp. 24,
    as used by the Cephes library.

raven `nx` (ISC)
----------------
The threefry2x32 PRNG hash in `src/random/threefry.ml` (the rotate/round
schedule, key-schedule parity constant, and two-word mixing) is adapted from
the raven `nx` numerical library, which is ISC licensed. The ISC license text
is reproduced verbatim in the top-level `LICENSE.raven` file. The numeric
results are additionally anchored bit-exactly to JAX v0.10.2
(`jax._src.random.threefry2x32`) via the checked-in goldens.
